ntrol the development and maintenance of complex microbial ecosystems. This book collects chapters that discuss the abiotic factors that structure arid and initial soil communities as well as the diversity and structure of the biological communities in these soils from viruses to plants.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aArid soils. 0aSoil biology. 4aEcology. 4aMicrobiology. 4aarid soils. 4adeserts. 4ainitial soils. 7aNATURE / Ecology.2bisacsh1 aAntoninka, Anita J.1 aAntoninka, Anita J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBabin, Doreen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBabin, Doreen.1 aBastida, F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBastida, Felipe.1 aBowker, Matthew A.1 aBowker, Matthew A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBüdel, Burkhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBüdel, Burkhard.1 aCowan, Don A.1 aCowan, Don A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEldridge, David J.1 aEldridge, David J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcia, Carlos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcia, Carlos.1 aGreen, T. G. Allan.1 aGreen, T.G. Allan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHamm, Paris S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHemkemeyer, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHemkemeyer, Michael.1 aHernandez, T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHernandez, Teresa.1 aKing, Gary M.1 aKing, Gary M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuske, Cheryl R., e